HDR Ladder Calibrated on Scientific Data: We have updated the exposure time pools by translating the data from Alberto Villa’s table (Astrofili Alta Valdera Association) directly into the code. The sequence now perfectly covers prominences (ultra-fast speeds) as well as the inner, middle, and outer corona (up to 2 seconds native exposure), optimized for an f/8 aperture and ISO 200.

Dynamic Stabilization Delay (Anti-Freeze): To prevent USB port collisions and software freezes, the set_shutter_speed function now calculates an intelligent wait time. If the set speed is faster than a quarter of a second, the delay remains minimal (0.15s); when switching to long exposures (0.5s, 1s, or 2s), the script automatically adds a delay proportional to the exposure duration itself, ensuring the shutter has physically closed before sending new commands.